RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELAWARE PARK RACE 1 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 82. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 27000. (PLUS UP TO 50% Other Sources) FOR FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD OR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED IN A CLAIMING RACE OF $25,000 OR LESS AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $40,000-$35,000. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since September 14, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since July 14, 2023 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $40,000, if for $35,00 0, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $25,000 Or Less Not Considered In Estimating Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WILL OR WON'T raced in the two path around the first turn, led the field up the backstretch, continued to show the way while saving ground around the far turn and in the lane and just held off a closer to the wire. DOCTOR ABBIE raced in the middle of the pack on the outside through the opening half mile, came around the far turn in the two path, began a bid passing the quarter pole and gained ground late. ALEXA'S DREAM raced in the two path early, settled off the pace on the outside for the run up the backstretch, navigated the far turn from the two and three path and passed tiring horses in the lane. PATTY CAKES was fractious in the gate, stumbled leaving it, saved ground around the first turn, tracked the leader on the inside up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the second turn and weakened in the final furlong. SIX THE HARD WAY chased the leader on the outside around the first turn and up the backstretch, came around the far bend in the two path and faded from there. INDY AGAIN saved ground early, raced off the pace on the inside up the backstretch, navigated the far turn from the two path and made no bid.

AMANI'S TIGER raced in the two path early, stalked the pace setter on the outside up the backstretch, came around the second turn in the three path, began a bid approaching the quarter pole and dueled to the wire to narrowly miss. MASTER MOJO raced off the pace on the outside through the opening half mile, navigated the far turn from the three and four path and improved position in the stretch. WORKING MAN hopped up leaving the gate, raced in the three path around the first bend, continued up the backstretch in the middle of the pack on the outside, came around the far turn still in the three path and finished evenly. THREE FOLD saved ground early, dueled on the inside up the backstretch, dropped back from the rail around the far turn and weakened in the lane. CHAMPAGNE JUAN saved ground around the first turn, chased the leader on the inside up the backstretch, continued around the second turn in the two path and faded from there. FOUR DAYS EARLY raced into traffic and steadied from the two path coming around the first turn, settled off the pace on the inside for the run up the backstretch, saved ground around the far turn and made no bid.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: HOP AND SCOTCH raced in the two path around the first turn, led the way up the backstretch, saved ground around the far turn and held clear to the finish. GUILLAUME raced off the pace in the two path around the first turn and up the backstretch, began a bid from the three path coming around the second turn and gained ground late. ULTIMATE IRONY raced at the back of the pack on the outside through the opening half mile, moved up while saving ground around the second turn and continued to improve position in the lane. Weight: 122 lbs. Non-Winners of a race other than maiden, claiming or starter allowed 3 lbs.; Maidens, 5 lbs. Starters to pass the entry box by the usual time of closing. CRAZY MASON raced off the pace in the two path through the opening half mile, began to move up while racing in the three path around the far turn and continued to improve position in the lane. REAL SENSATION saved ground around the first turn, trailed the field up the backstretch, continued around the far turn in the two path and never threatened. AMERICAN WAR HERO raced in the middle of the pack in the three path through the opening half mile, navigated the far turn from the two path and faded from there. WILLY D'S raced in the three path early, chased the leader between horses, dropped back while racing in the three path around the second turn and continued to tire while drifting out in the stretch. CATIRE VIZCAYA chased the pace setter from the two path through the opening half mile, dropped back while saving ground around the far turn and was empty in the lane.
